  "notes": "Skeleton. Yola (extinct English variety of Forth and Bargy, County Wexford), descended from Middle English. Idiosyncratic 18th-19th c. orthography; a broad English-like grapheme map is used and the elided leading apostrophe (e.g. 'cha) is unencoded. High PER expected.",
